3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates funding rates hourly based on the 1-hour TWAP premium between perpetual and spot prices. Funding payments occur automatically every hour at minute 0, with rates typically ranging from -0.05% to +0.15% depending on market sentiment. The exchange uses cross-margin by default, allowing efficient capital utilization across positions. Settlement happens on Starknet while order matching occurs off-chain for sub-second execution speeds."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","NEAR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT on RabbitX presents compelling arbitrage opportunities due to NEAR's active ecosystem development and moderate volatility patterns. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage while avoiding the crowded conditions of major pairs. NEAR's Layer 1 status creates distinct funding rate patterns compared to smaller altcoins, often showing predictable cycles during ecosystem announcements."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT funding rates on RabbitX have shown distinct patterns correlating with broader L1 narratives and NEAR ecosystem developments. During Q4 2023, funding rates averaged +0.08% hourly during Aurora and NEAR Protocol upgrades, while bear market periods saw rates drop to -0.02% as short interest dominated. The pair exhibits lower volatility in funding rates compared to newer L1s, with 90% of rates falling between -0.10% and +0.20%. Weekly cycles often show elevated positive funding on Mondays and Tuesdays, coinciding with institutional rebalancing patterns."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's hourly funding intervals create 24 daily arbitrage opportunities for NEAR/USDT, significantly more than 8-hour systems. The zero gas fee structure eliminates execution costs that typically erode small funding rate profits on other platforms. Optimal strategies involve monitoring funding rate predictions 15-30 minutes before settlement and executing delta-neutral positions across RabbitX and spot markets. The exchange's cross-margin system allows leveraging up to 10x, amplifying funding rate returns while maintaining reasonable risk levels."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR's correlation with Ethereum ecosystem developments introduces systematic risk that affects funding rate arbitrage profitability. Sudden NEAR Protocol announcements can cause rapid price gaps that exceed collected funding payments, particularly during low liquidity Asian trading hours. RabbitX's early-stage protocol status requires monitoring of smart contract risks and potential liquidity crunches during high volatility periods. Position sizing should account for NEAR's 24-hour volatility averaging 8-12%, with stop-losses set at 2-3x expected hourly funding to maintain positive risk-adjusted returns."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes NEAR/USDT funding rates different on RabbitX compared to centralized exchanges?","answer":"RabbitX's hourly funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities than the typical 8-hour cycles on CEXs. The Starknet-based infrastructure eliminates gas fees that would otherwise erode profits from small funding rate captures, making micro-arbitrage strategies viable."},{"question":"How does RabbitX's cross-margin affect NEAR funding rate strategies?","answer":"Cross-margin allows using unrealized PnL from other positions as collateral for NEAR trades, improving capital efficiency. This enables running multiple funding rate arbitrage strategies simultaneously while maintaining lower overall margin requirements compared to isolated margin systems."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate ranges for NEAR/USDT on RabbitX?","answer":"NEAR/USDT funding rates typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per hour, with extreme movements reaching ±0.30% during major NEAR ecosystem announcements. The pair shows less volatile funding compared to smaller L1 tokens due to NEAR's established market presence and diversified use cases."},{"question":"How does RabbitX's limited liquidity affect large NEAR funding rate arbitrage positions?","answer":"Position sizes above $50,000 may experience slippage during volatile periods due to RabbitX's developing liquidity. For optimal execution, break larger arbitrage positions into smaller chunks and monitor order book depth, especially during funding rate settlement windows when activity peaks."}]}]
